content:
Intents:
PC9876: User is submitting a request to purchase or receive a new laptop, pc or desktop computer.  
PC9875: User needs to return or hand in their old laptop, pc or desktop computer.
PC9874: User is experiencing some sort of issue with their laptop, pc or desktop computer.
PC9845: User is requesting an upgrade for their laptop, pc or desktop computer.  
NA0001: None of the above

Entities:
computer.brand: Dell, Lenovo, Mac
computer.type: laptop, pc, desktop

You will be given a sample that may contain more than one sentence. Your task is to assess the intent that the sample belongs to.  You should return only one intent. In addition, you should also identify any corresponding entities in the sample.  Your decision should be returned in YAML format. If a sample can belong to more than one intent, you should prioritize based on the following:

•	If PC9876 and PC9875 are returned, prioritize PC9876.
•	If PC9875 and PC9874 are returned, prioritize PC9874.
•	If PC9874 and PC9876 are returned, prioritize PC9874.
•	If PC9874 and PC9845 are returned, prioritize PC9874.
•	If PC9875 and PC9845 are returned, prioritize PC9875.
•	If PC9876 and PC9845 are returned, prioritize PC9876.
•	If three or more intents are returned, prioritize PC9874.
•	NA0001 should only be selected if none of the other intents apply.

Assess the following.  Again, remember that your output needs to be in YAML format, not json.  If you return your decision in json format you will be severely reprimanded and your answer will not bee deemed as valid.

My Dell computer won’t wake up!!!!! I need help or need to get a new one right away!!!!  I have a presentation tomorrow so this is URGENT!!!!!

rejected:
-   intent: PC9874
     entities:
         computer.brand: Dell
         computer.type: laptop
         problem: Won't wake up
         urgency: High
         entity.urgent: 'True'
